      "note_no": "84",
      "note": "Thus Razi interprets the phrase nad'u kulla unasin bi-imamihim (lit., \"We shall summon all human beings by [mentioning] their leaders\" or \"guides\"). In his opinion, the expression imdm (lit., \"leader\" or \"guide\") has in this context an abstract connotation, signifying the conscious disposition, good or bad, which governs a person's behaviour and provides the motives for his deeds. This interpretation is most convincing, and particularly so in view of the fundamental hadith quoted in my note 32 on 53:39."
